    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.6.0-dev+296-g1f49268c4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora release 34 (Thirty Four) x86_64 \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.23.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nAdd this line to init.lua\r\n```lua\r\nvim.o.undodir='~/.vim/undodir'\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpand '~'\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nNeovim treats the string like \"./\\~/.vim/undodir\" and create a directory named '~'",
