        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk Offering 4 options to do the same looks very annoying to maintain and offers no particular advantage as the respective environment variable is done as specified in POSIX.\r\n\r\n`~` is also less readable and not supported by all shells, ie in aliases. Also its annoying to parse.\r\nThe best practice shell way is to use `${HOME}`, but it should be sufficient to mention that `$` will cover every continuous [0-9|a-z|A-Z] instead of eagerly (and unsafely) expanding like shells do to have the simpler `$HOME`.\r\n\r\nThis behavior is also inconsistent with\r\n`:echo $HOME` returning both true in neovim and vim and `:echo ${HOME}` returning both an invalid expression.\r\nAnd `:echo ~` also returns an invalid expression for both. It would be very nice, if we could not use hacky shell stuff.",
